    "causal_summary": "User-verified on 2026-04-22 that Codex CLI sessions return \"no startup context observed\" and \"no advisor brief observed\" — identical user-visible symptoms to the Copilot CLI gap (sibling phase 004). Root cause is different: **Codex natively supports the hook transport**. The file `~/.codex/hooks.json` already registers `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, and `Stop` hooks — but only wires Superset's `notify.sh` (notification script), not Spec Kit Memory's advisor/context emitter.",
